WILLIAM Hague has made a speech in Glasgow arguing independence would be a"tragic mistake". Hague warns of making a 'tragic mistake' WILLIAM Hague has made a speech in Glasgow arguing independence would be a"tragic mistake".The Leader of the House of Commons and former Tory Party leader said: &quot;This vote is about the future of our family of nations, our family of united peoples.&quot;Our union, bound by common purpose and a rich history; and the great opportunities it offers to our young people.&quot;I am convinced that to tear asunder a union so proven, so precious and so durable would be a tragic mistake.&quot;He said independence was &quot;a leap in the dark&quot;. 